1. Copy allCountries.zip, Weather.csv to HDFS and WeatherAnalytics folder to CDH local system.

2. Run jar-file from Target folder in 3 steps :
	1)	spark-submit \ 
		--class UniqueStation \
		--master (local[n] or spark-port) 
		/_path_to_jar-file_/weather-analytics-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar \
		/_path_to_Weather-file_/Weather.csv \ 
		/_path_for_output_/
		
	2)	spark-submit \ 
		--class RegionStationMapper \
		--master (local[n] or spark-port) 
		/_path_to_jar-file_/weather-analytics-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar \
		/_path_to_1st_step_output_/part-00000 \ 
		/_path_to_allCountries-file_/allCountries.txt \ 
		/_path_for_output_/
		
	2)	spark-submit \ 
		--class RegionTemperature \
		--master (local[n] or spark-port) 
		/_path_to_jar-file_/weather-analytics-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar \
		/_path_to_Weather-file_/Weather.csv \ 
		/_path_to_2st_step_output_/part-00000 \ 
		/_path_for_all_time_analytics_output_/
		/_path_for_max_min_mean_analytics_output_/
		
	`*NOTES: All source-code is located in src/main/scala